articles.description: JoJo Cooper scored 23 points with seven rebounds and six assists and Wagner defeated Sacred Heart 99-84 on Thursday night to clinch at least a share of the Northeast Conference title.
articles.headline: Wagner clinches at least share of NEC title with 99-84 win

articles.description: Wajid Aminu scored a career-high 29 points and Ivan Gandia-Rosa dished out a career-high 18 assists as North Florida came back to beat SC Upstate 109-100 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Aminu, Gandia-Rosa lead high-flying Ospreys to victory

articles.description: Zach Brown misses the triple, but Shaquille Morris is there to clean up for the lay-in and the foul.
articles.headline: Morris' and-1 bucket gives the Shockers the lead

articles.description: Josh Reaves pokes the ball loose, runs the floor and Lamar Stevens gifts him with a pass for an uncontested dunk.
articles.headline: Reaves' pressure creates fast-break dunk for PSU

images.caption: Josh Reaves pokes the ball loose, runs the floor and Lamar Stevens gifts him with a pass for an uncontested dunk.

articles.description: Marvin Smith scored 18 points with four 3-pointers, leading four into double figures, and North Carolina Greensboro took control midway through the first half, defeating The Citadel 82-66 on Thursday.
articles.headline: Smith leads balanced UNC Greensboro past The Citadel 82-66

articles.headline: Penn State's Watkins beats everyone for alley-oop
